Please answer my code questions using the given API following this format: <<<api>>>: $API
<<<code>>>: $CODE
<<<explanation>>>: $EXPLANATION.
For API Iterator.next, the API usage rule is: Get the next element from an Iterator if it has more elements.

Question: How to print out an ArrayList<Integer> in a HashSet<ArrayList<Integer>>?: :How do you printout an index of type HashSet>?Here is the code:HashSet<ArrayList<Integer>> possibleRoutes;I tried int indexOfMinDistance = routesDistances.indexOf(Collections.min(routesDistances));System.out.println(possibleRoutes.indexOf(indexOfMinDistance));The programme suggests to cast possibleRoutes to List which produces more errors to the problem because they are not of the same type. So how do you print out an index, eg. an ArrayList<Integer>, of a HashSet<ArrayList<Integer>>?
Please using this api: Iterator.next.
Answer:
response:
<<<api>>>: Iterator.next()
<<<code>>>: 
Iterator<ArrayList<Integer>> iterator = possibleRoutes.iterator();
while (iterator.hasNext()) {
    ArrayList<Integer> route = iterator.next();
    System.out.println(possibleRoutes.indexOf(route));
}
<<<explanation>>>: To print out the index of each ArrayList<Integer> in the HashSet<ArrayList<Integer>>, you can use an Iterator to iterate over the elements of the HashSet. The Iterator.next() method returns the next element in the iteration. In this case, the elements are of type ArrayList<Integer>. You can then use the indexOf() method of the HashSet to get the index of the current element and print it out.
